Talking in your sleep
Some children speak at night
I do not mean those who wake up and tell us something about what happened the day before, but the children who speak during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it doesn’t matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called talking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Of course, more than one of you has been told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon may occur occasionally (once in life, for example, as during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child cannot remember anything.
There is not a single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, connections are sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic anxiety at night, enuresis noctura (betting at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for it.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stressful situations or overload.
In any case, this is a little explored phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It can be that you speak quietly in single words, whisper or it can be quite the opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and seek advice from a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes anxiety and arises in this way.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is perform a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to arouse the child before sleeping.
So, choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are horrible and a little too wild.
For the nervous children to whom relaxation is recommended, relaxation methods can be used to help them get some inner peace.
This helps the child sleep quietly.
If speaking occurs during sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless to the child and the next day he will not be able to remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will tear him out of sleep.
Even though the child speaks, he sleeps, so he rests.
Remember, if he shows up scared after a couple of appearances, it is recommended to seek advice or find out what the reason the child is afraid of.
If they understand what it says (which is not so common), the child does not put pressure to conduct an interrogation and get more information out.
So you will not be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child is asleep, he is unconscious and cannot think about it.
Besides, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it dreams and why it says it, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Perhaps, it does not tell the child that you hear this at night and know its secrets.
Not even as a joke.
It causes a lot of fear.
So, don’t worry, it’s nothing bad, it’s a moment that only takes a few minutes.
